  <description type="morphology">Plants slender (long-branched). Involucres campanulate, 5.5–6.5 mm. Phyllaries in 4–5 series, squarrose, acute to acuminate, densely strigillose, sparsely stipitate-glandular; mid 0.7–1 mm wide. 2n = 10, 20.</description>
  <description type="phenology">Flowering late Aug–early Nov.</description>
  <description type="habitat">Dry oak-pine and oak-hickory woodlands;</description>
  <description type="elevation">0–800+ m;</description>
  <description type="distribution">Ala., Ark., Fla., Ga., Kans., La., Md., Miss., Mo., N.C., Okla., S.C., Tenn., Tex., Va.</description>
  <number>13b.</number>
  <discussion>Variety gracile is most common in the southwestern part of the species range, in the western Coastal Plains and Central Lowland, and is infrequent to the east. It is mostly diploid, some tetraploids occurring in Texas and Louisiana.</discussion>
